ng financing, morale crises, and succession. With each president contributing a chapter, covering her or his own years in office, Leading the Modern University reveals that large public institutions have internal dynamics and external forces that supersede any individual leader’s years in office. This is a case study for those interested in organizational change as seen by the leadership of a major public institution during a dynamic period in higher education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCollege presidentszOntariozTorontoxHistory. 0aUniversities and collegeszOntariozTorontoxHistory. 7aEDUCATION / Administration / Higher.2bisacsh1 aHarry, Arthurs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacdonald, H. Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMann, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarsden, Lorna R ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarsden, Lorna R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSden, Lorna R . Mar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShoukri, Mamdouh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261761240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442617612423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442617612.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles